		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Mask (computing)</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>In <a href="/wiki/Computer_science" title="Computer science">computer science</a>, a <b>mask</b> is data that is used for <a href="/wiki/Bitwise_operation" title="Bitwise operation">bitwise operations</a>.</p>
<p>Using a mask, multiple bits in a byte, <a href="/wiki/Nibble" title="Nibble">nibble</a>, word (etc.) can be set either on, off or inverted from on to off (or vice versa) in a single bitwise operation.</p>
